The paper presents a system based on Answer Set Programming (ASP) for the automatic generation of teams of employees in the seaport of Gioia Tauro. This involves solving a complex optimization problem with several constraints, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of ASP indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The problem of team building in the seaport involves managing resources and scheduling, which could also make the paper relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper describes a system that is currently being used in a real-world setting, which could make it relevant to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
